As the lobster industry shows, they’ll create new winners and losers based on nationality rather than competitiveness.
Perhaps more than any other U.S. sector, the lobster industry has been buffeted by tariffs.
The lobster industry, which has experienced a rare triple whammy of tariff hits, is a peek at how this new world might work.
Then on June 15, the industry learned that in response to Mr. Trump’s tariffs on China, China would retaliate with a 25 percent tariff on various seafood, including lobster.
The clear winners of the lobster tariff wars are the Canadian dealers.